# EAS Build upload scope (repo root).
#
# EAS Build archives the GIT REPOSITORY ROOT, not the directory eas.json lives
# in. The only EAS-built app in this monorepo is packages/mobile, so without
# this file every `eas build` would upload the entire Next.js + Electron
# desktop app too. .easignore uses .gitignore syntax and overrides .gitignore
# for EAS uploads; it is read only by the EAS CLI and affects nothing else.
#
# Whitelist just packages/mobile (the "ignore everything except one subdir"
# idiom: ignore each level, then re-include the path down to the app).
/*
!packages/
packages/*
!packages/mobile/

# Within the mobile app, still drop heavy/generated dirs that EAS regenerates
# on its build servers (these are also in packages/mobile/.gitignore, but
# .easignore must restate them since it replaces .gitignore for EAS).
packages/mobile/node_modules/
packages/mobile/ios/
packages/mobile/android/
packages/mobile/.expo/
packages/mobile/dist/
packages/mobile/web-build/

# CRITICAL: .easignore REPLACES .gitignore for the EAS upload, so the
# secret/local patterns .gitignore protects must be restated or the whitelist
# above would upload them from a developer's machine. (No-slash patterns match
# at any depth; listed last so they win even inside the whitelisted dir.)
*.p12
*.p8
*.key
*.jks
*.mobileprovision
*.pem
*.cer
*.keystore
# All env files (mirrors the root .gitignore's `.env*` + `!.env.example`).
# Must be the broad `.env*`, not just `.env*.local`: a local `eas build` from a
# dev workstation would otherwise upload an uncommitted `.env` / `.env.production`
# (potential secrets) since .easignore replaces .gitignore (Codex P1 on #747).
.env*
!.env.example
.DS_Store
*.tsbuildinfo
expo-env.d.ts
.metro-health-check*
